<br>
We are almost all CoV aligned, most of us max ally.  We've been killing in the Halls of Testing for the past couple of months.  I'd like to gather some information about what's involved in fighting in NToV before I propose reducing our CoV faction ;-)<br>
<br>
1.  How tough, in general terms, are the NON-BOSS mobs in North ToV?  Roughly comparable to Halls of Testing/West Wing?  Tougher?  Anything special that would give us a rude surprise?<br>
<br>
2.  Exactly what factions hits do you take for regular non-boss mobs in NToV?  Negative CoV, I assume ... any plusses to Zek or Rif or negatives to Coldain?  About how badly a hit to ally CoV would we take killing all the mobs we need to to get to PoM?<br>
<br>
3.  About how many mobs are there total between the entrance to North ToV, and the PoM entrance?  I've looked at some maps, including ones with partial spawn points on them ... would you suggest going clockwise around to the left or counter-clockwise around to the right?<br>
<br>
4.  What kind of &quot;incentive&quot; loot is possible from the non-boss NToV mobs?  The only one I know about (being a shaman) is the Shield of Wurms from &quot;named&quot; drakes ... anything else?<br>
<br>
Thanks in advance, appreciate any answers including general advice and feasability ;-)<br>
<br>
Qualm, Barbarian Shaman, E'ci <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usanatarium.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sanatarium </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/26/02 12:53:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10484.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: General questions about North ToV &gt;&gt; PoM</span><hr size=1> The majority of the non-boss mobs are the same as any other mob in HoT, West Wing, etc. However, wyverns are a pain to pull. Always rampaging and cause alot of havoc.  I can't shed much info on pulling them since I'm not a monk. <br>
<br>
Getting there, I don't see any way being better, but you will have to deal with Flurry drakes. You can tell them apart by either having a special name to them, or being A_X_Defender. These things flurry with the best of them.<br>
<br>
Some of the mobs will give you +Zek, -CoV, and something else, it's a - hit, but once you move in, all of the flurry drakes, named drakes, and dragons if you happened to kill them will give you a -Guardians of Veeshan, and -CoV hit. No positives. A guess would say there's 80? mobs from entrance of ToV to PoM. That's counting all of the baby drakes you have to kill before you can move up into the pit to move around, unless they are on CoV faction. I was once on CoV faction, but killed it before doing North Wing, so I can't say if the baby drakes are KoS to everyone or not.<br>
<br>
Incentive loot would be a shield for each of the shield classes, a neck item for all of the melee classes, and a caster only shield that is very good. All of these are fairly good items, and seem to drop like candy off of the named drakes and guards.<br>
<br>
As for how much of a CoV hit you would take, I would think it would be a pretty good one, possibly down to KoS if you cleared all the flurries and the fire wurms near PoM entrance. Unless all the dragons are dead however, you will get stuck with Eashen of the Sky, Aaryonar, and either Dagarn or Koi'Doken being in your way of getting there. Even though most are rooted, there are some still in the way to block people passing through. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/um0j00rising.showPublicProfile?language=EN>m0j00rIsIng</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/26/02 12:56:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10484.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: General questions about North ToV &gt;&gt; PoM</span><hr size=1> I guessthe biggest thing u need to worry about are the flurry drakes, if u arent prepared for them 1 of them can wipe out 30 plus people pretty quick.  Best thing to do is rotate warrior defensives and have all healers on that warrior, pretty basic principle.  Im guessing u guys plan on  making trip to pom after ntov cleared?  If thats the case try and go the day after all the named were clear, would mean less flurry drakes and getting to pom shouldnt take u more then 2 hours tops.  As far as faction goes, if u are planning on JUST going to pom then its nothing 1 or 2 nights in the arena couldnt fix.  As far as other mobs go only other tough one are the ancient guardians and those arent too much tougher then hot mobs. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubaradenthala.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Baraden ThaLa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/26/02 12:57:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10484.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: General questions about North ToV &gt;&gt; PoM</span><hr size=1> green flurry drakes are the worst <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :x --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/sick.gif ALT=":x"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubaradenthala.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Baraden ThaLa</A> at: 3/26/02 12:58:09 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uilltair.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Illtair</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/26/02 1:05:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10484.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: General questions about North ToV &gt;&gt; PoM</span><hr size=1> I'm assuming you're going to go in after someone else has cleared the dragons out.<br>
<br>
Also, POM is a lot of fun to mess around in the first few times...but it will be boring as hell after a couple days though, just so you know.  Some people will get DR flowers, maybe PR, try to start other quests, realize its a waste of time, and move back to better XP and loot venues that are easier to get to.  Most melee's don't want to live in POM, so unless you set up a locket of escape recharge and bind thing, have fun with your all caster groups! <br>
<br>
1. The first mobs to worry about clearing are big wyverns that rampage like crazy.  Be ready to heal multiple people.  Farther in, flurry drakes will own you badly if you aren't ready for them, especially if you get more than one.  Much harder than HOT mobs.  Have a def war ready for each one, and get your monks to pull them single. <br>
<br>
2. Most mobs in NTOV are on Guardians of Veeshan faction.  When you kill GOV mobs you get -GOV -COV.  There are a couple COV mobs in there as well though, including mini-drakes and some normal drakes that you'd find in the front of the zone.  Killing COV is -COV -Yeli +Zek iirc.<br>
<br>
3. Go right.  Don't know mob count - it will depend what is repoped when you enter as well.  If you go immediately after someone else has cleared NTOV, not a whole lot will be up.<br>
<br>
4. Named drakes' loot table consists of a class specific shield or choker for everyone except rangers who get a bow, and all int casters use the barrier of sound.  Also can drop ring of superiority. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufashidusct.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fashidus CT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/26/02 1:07:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10484.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: General questions about North ToV &gt;&gt; PoM</span><hr size=1> Be friendly with another NTOV ready guild, have a druid and mage follow them to the POM cubby, gate the druid and coh everyone up. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uqualm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qualm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/26/02 1:21:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10484.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: General questions about North ToV &gt;&gt; PoM</span><hr size=1> Nice responses so far, thank you ;-)<br>
<br>
1.  Yes we would only attempt it with the boss dragons dead, and yes we are friendly with two of the groups/guilds that do North ToV regularly, but part of the draw is the excitement of fighting through (what we can handle anyway) so I am not planning to simply get CoH'd in ...<br>
<br>
2.  What is the respawn on the &quot;flurry drakes&quot;?  Is it 72 minutes like the normal mobs or 7 days like the dragons?<br>
Are they at specific spots or can they spawn as any normal mob?<br>
<br>
3.  We would all hopefully be above dubious to CoV till we are well past the mini-drakes, so I don't expect to have to fight them.  Unless they assist mobs we do have to fight near them or pull past them?<br>
<br>
4.  I just want to get us to PoM, and maybe spend the next day or two wandering around, I don't really expect us to camp it or quest it at this point.<br>
<br>
Thanks for the responses so far ;-)<br>
<br>
Qualm, Barbarian Shaman, E'ci <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufashidusct.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fashidus CT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/26/02 1:31:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10484.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: General questions about North ToV &gt;&gt; PoM</span><hr size=1> The baby drakes are kos.  Guilds that are KOS to COV do coh to just before the babies.  You can avoid the 4 big drakes where Eashen pops if you hug the wall. <br>
<br>
Rotate tanks with defensive on the flurries.  There are like 10+.. named and A X Defender as someone else mentioned.  Nice drops...   Your pull team is the most important tho..   and tank mezzing adds.  You've done HoT so that should be in order.<br>
<br>
Also.... Kael quest pieces drop... screw COV faction if you get some nice pieces <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufashidusct.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fashidus CT</A> at: 3/26/02 1:48:44 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujeters.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jeters</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/26/02 1:38:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10484.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: General questions about North ToV &gt;&gt; PoM</span><hr size=1> Honestly, you're going to want to treat every flurry drake pull like you are killing Vindicator. <br>
<br>
Honestly, if you have only been doing HoT mobs a few months (which are much easier than WWing, which are easier than Ntov) you should either be prepared for multiple wipeouts (which happen sometimes in north to even the most experienced of raiders)--or think of an alternate way to bring your guild to PoM. <br>
Even if the boss mobs arent up (which is hard to have ALL of them down except directly after a clearing) a single flurry drake can own a large raid that isnt fully prepared. <br>
<br>
I know eashen's pets are 72 minutes, unsure about the other drakes in there. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=yayanono>Yayanono</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/26/02 1:51:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10484.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> drakes</span><hr size=1> A xxxx Defender(note capitalized) respawn in 4 hours.<br>
<br>
The named ones xxx the Crimson Fang or whatever are 7 days.<br>
<br>
4 named flurries and 4 unnamed flurries in North wing.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utwiggietymberwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twiggie Tymberwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/26/02 1:56:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10484.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: General questions about North ToV &gt;&gt; PoM</span><hr size=1> Flurry drakes hit for 750 and Flurry every round.  They have roughly 100k hp.<br>
<br>
Wyverns rampage every round and hit for 350ish.<br>
<br>
You will need to clear the rotundra to be able to pull the wyverns.  From the NToV door there are roughly:<br>
<br>
8 Wyverns<br>
10 baby drakes<br>
~30 drakes<br>
6 Flurry Drakes<br>
2 wurms<br>
<br>
